OL,6,F"The Law Officers reviewed the
OL,7,Fevidence, and also passed it to
OL,8,Fexternal lawyers to review. As in all
OL,9,Fcases being considered for criminal
OL,10,Fprosecution, the 'Decision to
OL,11,FProsecute Code of Guidance', which is
OL,12,Fa public document available on the Law
OL,13,FOfficers' website, was then applied
OL,14,Fand this led to the decision to take
OL,15,Fthe matter no further.
OL,17,F"The alleged crimes were many years
OL,18,Fbefore he was a police officer, and
OL,19,Fthe fact he is a serving police
OL,20,Fofficer was not relevant to the
OL,21,Fdecision made in this case.
